Synopis:

Inspired by the Book of Ruth from Hebrew scriptures, the Moabitess child Ruth is sold to the temple of Chemosh (pronounced KEM-osh). Years pass and she serves as a priestess to the idol.

While arranging a temple ritual, she encounters a Judean family of artisans: Elimelech, his wife Naomi, their sons Chilion and Mahlon, and daughter-in-law Orpah. Ruth is curious about their God, and begins to meet secretly with Mahlon. After tragedy strikes, Ruth follows Naomi and begins a new life in Bethlehem of Judah
